How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Amazon Customer
5 out of 5 stars
A nice "basic" button up
It's very hard to find a unassuming button up that is not prone to horrendous wrinkles, attracts bits of fuzz and hair, has a weird cut or fabric thickness issues. This shirt checks all those boxes. It's not silk, but it feels similar. They are a little bit slippery feeling. Been wearing it all day at work and it's still looks good. I think they will hold up well in the wash. Out of the box it's a little wrinkly, but does relax. The sleeves are a little long on me 5'6" female wearing M (shown rolled over once), but I'll be wearing it rolled up most of the time. I bought some other colors, I think these will be good business casual shirts.
